Tomorrow: What do I think about this film?

This film is visually stunning and does an exceptional job at grabbing the audiences' attention by showing examples of how climate change can affect us environmentally and as a community.
This film also portrays a well developed plot as it teaches a valuable and important lesson about climate change and how it is negatively impacting us. It explores the reality of human nature and how itтАЩs damaging our health, the environment, and surrounding ecosystems.
This film is very educational as it exposes the reality we live in to younger generations. This helps kids expand their knowledge on this issue which brings in awareness of whatтАЩs happening around them; by giving them a better understanding of how we are ruining the planet and our role in global warming. Additionally, it's worth mentioning that it is a smart idea to create a short film about this issue as it is a great method to reach kids.
This is the case as most forms of media that cover this topic are more directed towards teens and adults (eg. documentaries). Therefore, the film discusses an important topic in a kid friendly fashion that allows children to understand a serious topic like climate change.
Lastly, this film also discusses about the importance of taking action which is crucial in order to save the planet from irreversible damage. What I took from watching this film is that we can all something to create a change for the better. I hope that those watching this film also feel the same way.
Finally, I would like to congratulate Soto Mama(Mohammad Shihab Uddin) and the whole team behind this brilliant film as I feel like their vision will do good for the community and towards a positive impact on the environment. Well done!

Trina, Grade 12
Toronto, Canada
